com.appdynamics.instrumentation.sdk.template

Class AInfoPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.appdynamics.instrumentation.sdk.ASDKPlugin
      • com.appdynamics.instrumentation.sdk.template.AInfoPoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRuleAppliable

    public abstract class AInfoPoint
extends ASDKPlugin
    This class serves as the template for Information Points for consumers of the Instrumentation SDK. Anything inserted into the ISDKMetricContext by the storeMetrics method will be reported as a Custom Metric. Created by ryan.terbush on 3/10/16.

      • storeMetrics

        public abstract void storeMetrics(java.lang.Object invokedObject,
                                  java.lang.String className,
                                  java.lang.String methodName,
                                  java.lang.Object[] paramValues,
                                  java.lang.Throwable thrownException,
                                  java.lang.Object returnValue,
                                  ISDKMetricContext sdkContext)
                           throws ReflectorException
        This method is a place to stash metrics in the provided ISDKMetricContext via ISDKMetricContext.storeMetric(String, String, Long). Any metrics stored there will be reported by the agent. The agent will clear the context after every invocation.
        Parameters:
        invokedObject - The invoked object
        className - The name of the class this method was called on.
        methodName - The name of the method invoked.
        paramValues - The parameters of the invoked method
        thrownException - The exception thrown by this invocation of the method.
        returnValue - The return value of the method
        sdkContext - The context to store metrics in
        Throws:
        ReflectorException
